President Obama hosted an Evening Hanukkah Reception at the White House, where he spoke about the significance of Hanukkah and the importance of standing up against bigotry and discrimination. He also highlighted the story of Manny Lindenbaum, a Holocaust survivor who biked 200 miles through Europe to raise money for refugee children from Darfur. The President emphasized the power of faith over fear and invited Rabbi Sid Schwarz to lead the blessing and help light the candles.